HEADWORD: Windflower
<hw>Wind"flow`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The anemone; -- so called because formerly supposed to open only
when the wind was blowing. See <er>Anemone</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

